<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-02-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-02-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="270" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d270">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">5727/177.</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Netherlands
                                        Chargé</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Royal Legation of the Netherlands</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-02-13"><hi rend="italic">February 13, 1908</hi></date>.</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 150.]</seg></opener>
                            <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>: In reply to the
                                department’s note of January 16, I have the honor to inclose a copy
                                of the Bulletin of the Laws of Kingdom of Holland, No. 76, 1896, in
                                which will be found the royal decree of May 4, 1896, concerning the
                                general regulations of chambers of commerce in the Netherlands.</p>
                            <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. A.
                                Royaards.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>